[normal]Written evidence submitted by the Electoral Commission (DWB 09)[bold]Introduction[bold] [bold]1.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Electoral Commission is an independent body which reports directly to the UK Parliament. We regulate political party and 
[normal]election finance and set standards for well-run elections. We put voters first by working to support a healthy democracy, where elections and referendums are based on our principles of trust, participation, and no undue influence. We are responsible for pu
[normal]blishing reports on the administration of elections
[normal] and referendums
[normal]. 
[normal]1.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]O
[normal]ur comments on the 
[normal]draft 
[normal]Bill relate to matters concerning referendums and 
[normal]electoral arrangements
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]Referendum about commencement of income tax provisions[bold]1.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
